# CSS engine floor (single source) for the Lightning CSS transformer.
# vite.config.ts reads these explicit floors via scripts/browserslist_targets.mjs
# and feeds them to lightningcss browserslistToTargets(), so the floor lives in
# exactly one place and is never hand-typed as a target object.
#
# Floor rationale (max of the per-feature minimums, primary sourced): :has() binds
# Firefox 121; native CSS nesting (a later-phase adopt target) binds Chrome 120 and
# Safari 17.2; mobile Safari / WebKit is a first-class target (state.md decision 14),
# so the iOS floor matches Safari.
Chrome >= 120
Firefox >= 121
Safari >= 17.2
iOS >= 17.2
